<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Required_resource_arm  Entity: Required_resource_by_resource_item  
   <express_ref linkend="required_resource:arm:Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_by_resource_item"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_by_resource_item">
A <b>Required_resource_by_resource_item</b> is a statement of a required resource that can be identified within the application context.
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Required_resource_arm  Entity: Required_resource_by_resource_item  Attribute: resource_item 
   <express_ref linkend="required_resource:arm:Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_by_resource_item.resource_item"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_by_resource_item.resource_item">
a reference to an item that is defined as a resource within the application context. 
It can refer to an actual as well as to a type of resource.
<example>
Tool kit, facility, and  product category are examples of resource items.
</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Required_resource_arm  Entity: Required_resource_by_specification  
   <express_ref linkend="required_resource:arm:Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_by_specification"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_by_specification">
A statement of a required resource that is specified. A required resource that is specified may have multiple
different realizations. 
</ext_description>
<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Required_resource_arm  Entity: Required_resource_relationship  
   <express_ref linkend="required_resource:arm:Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_relationship"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
<ext_description linkend="Required_resource_arm.Required_resource_relationship">
A <b>Required_resource_relationship</b> is a relationship between two required resource statements. The meaning of the relationship is determined by classification.
<example number="1">
"Alternative" and "Realized_by" are examples of required resource relationship.
</example>
<example number="2">
A required_resource_by_specification for a power supply can be realized by a required_resource_by_resource_item with part
number "ABC-1234".
</example>
</ext_description>
